revisions.description: Initial version of this MIB module.

tpIgmpSnoopingEnable.name: tpIgmpSnoopingEnable
tpIgmpSnoopingEnable.description: Select Enable/Disable IGMP Snooping function globally on the Switch. 0. disable 1. enable

tpUnknownMulticastPacket.name: tpUnknownMulticastPacket
tpUnknownMulticastPacket.description: Select the operation for the switch to process unknown multicast. 0. forward 1. discard

tpUnknownReportSuppression.name: tpUnknownReportSuppression
tpUnknownReportSuppression.description: Select Enable/Disable IGMP Snooping report suppression function globally on the Switch. 0. disable 1. enable

tpIgmpGlobalRouterTime.name: tpIgmpGlobalRouterTime
tpIgmpGlobalRouterTime.description: Specify the aging time of the router port. Within this time, if the switch don't receive IGMP query message from the router port, it will consider this port is not a router port any more,60-600 second.

tpIgmpGlobalMemberTime.name: tpIgmpGlobalMemberTime
tpIgmpGlobalMemberTime.description: Specify the aging time of the member port. Within this time, if the switch don't receive IGMP report message from the member port, it will consider this port is not a member port any more,60-600 second.

tpIgmplastListenerQueryInterval.name: tpIgmplastListenerQueryInterval
tpIgmplastListenerQueryInterval.description: Enter the Last Listener Query interval time. When the multicast group has no more member ports, it will send the Specific Query Message with this interval time to check whether there is another member. The interval is ranging from 1 to 5 seconds.

tpIgmplastListenerQueryCount.name: tpIgmplastListenerQueryCount
tpIgmplastListenerQueryCount.description: Enter the Last Listener Query numbers. When the multicast group has no more member ports, it will send this numbers of Specific Query Message to check whether there is another member. It is ranging from 1 to 5.

tpIgmpPortTable.name: tpIgmpPortTable
tpIgmpPortTable.description: IGMP Snooping (Internet Group Management Protocol Snooping) is a multicast control mechanism running on Layer 2 switch. It can effectively prevent multicast groups being broadcasted in the network.

tpIgmpPortEntry.name: tpIgmpPortEntry
tpIgmpPortEntry.description: An entry contains of the information of port configure.

tpIgmpSnoopingPortEnable.name: tpIgmpSnoopingPortEnable
tpIgmpSnoopingPortEnable.description: Select Enable/Disable IGMP Snooping for the desired port. 0. Disable 1. Enable

tpIgmpFastLeavePortEnable.name: tpIgmpFastLeavePortEnable
tpIgmpFastLeavePortEnable.description: Select Enable/Disable Fast Leave feature for the desired port. If Fast Leave is enabled for a port, the Switch will immediately remove this port from the multicast group upon receiving IGMP leave messages. 0. Disable 1. Enable

tpIgmpPortLag.name: tpIgmpPortLag
tpIgmpPortLag.description: Displays the LAG number which the port belongs to.

tpIgmpVlanTable.name: tpIgmpVlanTable
tpIgmpVlanTable.description: Multicast groups established by IGMP Snooping are based on VLANs. You can configure different IGMP parameters for different VLANs.

tpIgmpVlanEntry.name: tpIgmpVlanEntry
tpIgmpVlanEntry.description: An entry contains of the information of igmpsnooping.

tpIgmpVlanId.name: tpIgmpVlanId
tpIgmpVlanId.description: Enter the VLAN ID to enable IGMP Snooping for the desired VLAN,1-4094.

tpIgmpRouterTime.name: tpIgmpRouterTime
tpIgmpRouterTime.description: Specify the aging time of the router port. Within this time, if the switch don't receive IGMP query message from the router port, it will consider this port is not a router port any more,0,60-600 second.

tpIgmpMemberTime.name: tpIgmpMemberTime
tpIgmpMemberTime.description: Specify the aging time of the member port. Within this time, if the switch don't receive IGMP report message from the member port, it will consider this port is not a member port any more,0,60-600 second.

tpIgmpRouterPort.name: tpIgmpRouterPort
tpIgmpRouterPort.description: Config the static router ports which are mainly used in the network with stable topology.

tpIgmpForbiddenRouterPort.name: tpIgmpForbiddenRouterPort
tpIgmpForbiddenRouterPort.description: Config the forbidden router ports which are mainly used to forbidden specified ports to become router ports.

tpIgmpVlanStatus.name: tpIgmpVlanStatus
tpIgmpVlanStatus.description: the following two values are states: these values may be read or written active(1), notInService(2), the following value is a state: this value may be read, but not written notReady(3), the following three values are actions: these values may be written, but are never read createAndGo(4), createAndWait(5), destroy(6)

tpIgmpMultiVlanId.name: tpIgmpMultiVlanId
tpIgmpMultiVlanId.description: Enter the VLAN ID of the multicast VLAN,2-4094.If enter 0, multicast VLAN is disabled.

tpIgmpMultitRouterTime.name: tpIgmpMultitRouterTime
tpIgmpMultitRouterTime.description: Specify the aging time of the router port. Within this time, if the switch don't receive IGMP query message from the router port, it will consider this port is not a router port any more,0,60-600 second.

tpIgmpMultiMemberTime.name: tpIgmpMultiMemberTime
tpIgmpMultiMemberTime.description: Specify the aging time of the member port. Within this time, if the switch don't receive IGMP report message from the member port, it will consider this port is not a member port any more,0,60-600 second.

tpIgmpMultiRouterPort.name: tpIgmpMultiRouterPort
tpIgmpMultiRouterPort.description: Config the static router ports which are mainly used in the network with stable topology.

tpIgmpMultiForbiddenRouterPort.name: tpIgmpMultiForbiddenRouterPort
tpIgmpMultiForbiddenRouterPort.description: Config the forbidden router ports which are mainly used to forbidden specified ports to become router ports.

tpIgmpMultiReplaceSrcIp.name: tpIgmpMultiReplaceSrcIp
tpIgmpMultiReplaceSrcIp.description: config the source ip which will replace the source ip of IGMP report in multicast vlan.

igmpQuerierTable.name: igmpQuerierTable
igmpQuerierTable.description: IGMP Snooping Querier is based on VLAN. You can configure different IGMP Snooping Querier parameters for different VLANs.

igmpQuerierEntry.name: igmpQuerierEntry
igmpQuerierEntry.description: An entry contains of the information of IGMP Snooping Querier.

igmpQuerierVlanId.name: igmpQuerierVlanId
igmpQuerierVlanId.description: Enter the VLAN ID to enable IGMP Snooping Querier for the desired VLAN, ranging from 1 to 4094.

queryInterval.name: queryInterval
queryInterval.description: Enter the Query message interval time. The Querier will send General Query Message with this interval. The interval is ranging from 10 to 300 seconds.

maxResponseTime.name: maxResponseTime
maxResponseTime.description: Enter the value of Maximum Response Time field of the Query message. The host is expected to response to an IGMP general query within this time. The time is ranging from 1 to 25 seconds.

generalQuerySrcIp.name: generalQuerySrcIp
generalQuerySrcIp.description: Enter the General Query Message source IP address.

igmpQuerierStatus.name: igmpQuerierStatus
igmpQuerierStatus.description: The following values are states: these values may be used as follow: active(1),if the entry is being used. createAndGo(4),not being used. destroy(6),destory the entry.

tpIgmpFilterPortTable.name: tpIgmpFilterPortTable
tpIgmpFilterPortTable.description: When the switch receives IGMP report message, it examines the multicast filtering IP ID configured on the access port to determine if the port can join the multicast group. If the multicast IP is not filtered, the switch will add the port to the forward port list of the multicast group. Otherwise, the switch will drop the IGMP report message. In that way, you can control the multicast groups that users can access.

tpIgmpFilterPortEntry.name: tpIgmpFilterPortEntry
tpIgmpFilterPortEntry.description: An entry contains of the information of a port param.

tpIgmpFilterMaxGroup.name: tpIgmpFilterMaxGroup
tpIgmpFilterMaxGroup.description: Specify the maximum number of multicast groups to prevent some ports taking up too much bandwidth.

tpIgmpFilterMaxGroupAction.name: tpIgmpFilterMaxGroupAction
tpIgmpFilterMaxGroupAction.description: The policy should be taken when the number of multicast group a port has joined reach the maximum. 0.Drop: drop the successive report packet, and this port can not join any other multicast group. 1.Replace: when the port joins another new multicast group,it will quit the existing multicast group randomly.

tpIgmpFilterBindAddrId.name: tpIgmpFilterBindAddrId
tpIgmpFilterBindAddrId.description: Enter the profile ID the port will be bound to. Only one profile can be bound to each port.

tpIgmpFilterPortLag.name: tpIgmpFilterPortLag
tpIgmpFilterPortLag.description: Displays the LAG number which the port belongs to.

tpIgmpAuthPortTable.name: tpIgmpAuthPortTable
tpIgmpAuthPortTable.description: IGMP Authentication can control the access of multicast packets.

tpIgmpAuthPortEntry.name: tpIgmpAuthPortEntry
tpIgmpAuthPortEntry.description: An entry contains of the information of port authentication configure.

tpIgmpAuthEnable.name: tpIgmpAuthEnable
tpIgmpAuthEnable.description: Select Enable/Disable IGMP Authentication for the desired port. 0. Disable 1. Enable

tpIgmpAuthPortLag.name: tpIgmpAuthPortLag
tpIgmpAuthPortLag.description: Displays the LAG number which the port belongs to.

tpIgmpGlobalAuthAccountConfigEable.name: tpIgmpGlobalAuthAccountConfigEable
tpIgmpGlobalAuthAccountConfigEable.description: 0. disable 1. enable Enable/Disable the IGMP Authentication Accounting.

tpIgmpPktStatTable.name: tpIgmpPktStatTable
tpIgmpPktStatTable.description: A list of multicast statistic Table.

tpIgmpPktStatEntry.name: tpIgmpPktStatEntry
tpIgmpPktStatEntry.description: An entry contains of multicast packet statistics over each port.

tpIgmpQueryPktStat.name: tpIgmpQueryPktStat
tpIgmpQueryPktStat.description: Displays the number of query packets the port received.

tpIgmpReportV1PktStat.name: tpIgmpReportV1PktStat
tpIgmpReportV1PktStat.description: Displays the number of IGMPv1 report packets the port received.

tpIgmpReportV2PktStat.name: tpIgmpReportV2PktStat
tpIgmpReportV2PktStat.description: Displays the number of IGMPv2 report packets the port received.

tpIgmpReportV3PktStat.name: tpIgmpReportV3PktStat
tpIgmpReportV3PktStat.description: Displays the number of IGMPv3 report packets the port received.

tpIgmpLeavePktStat.name: tpIgmpLeavePktStat
tpIgmpLeavePktStat.description: Displays the number of leave packets the port received.

tpIgmpErrorPktStat.name: tpIgmpErrorPktStat
tpIgmpErrorPktStat.description: Displays the number of error packets the port received.

tpIgmpMulticastGroupTable.name: tpIgmpMulticastGroupTable
tpIgmpMulticastGroupTable.description: A list of multicast groups Table.

tpIgmpMulticastGroupEntry.name: tpIgmpMulticastGroupEntry
tpIgmpMulticastGroupEntry.description: An entry contains of multicast packet statistics over each port.

tpIgmpForwardPorts.name: tpIgmpForwardPorts
tpIgmpForwardPorts.description: Displays the forward ports of multicast group.

tpIgmpGrouptype.name: tpIgmpGrouptype
tpIgmpGrouptype.description: Displays the type of multicast group.

tpIgmpMulticastStaticGroupTable.name: tpIgmpMulticastStaticGroupTable
tpIgmpMulticastStaticGroupTable.description: A list of multicast groups Table.

tpIgmpMulticastStaticGroupEntry.name: tpIgmpMulticastStaticGroupEntry
tpIgmpMulticastStaticGroupEntry.description: An entry contains of multicast packet statistics over each port.

tpIgmpStaticForwardPorts.name: tpIgmpStaticForwardPorts
tpIgmpStaticForwardPorts.description: The forward ports of multicast group.

tpIgmpStaticGroupStatus.name: tpIgmpStaticGroupStatus
tpIgmpStaticGroupStatus.description: The following values are states: these values may be used as follow: active(1),if the entry is being used. notInService(2),destory the entry. notReady(3),destory the entry. createAndGo(4),not being used createAndWait(5),creat a new entry destroy(6),destory the entry.
